{"lemma":"فِتْنَة","slug":"فِتْنَة","root":"ف.ت.ن","root_slug":"ف-ت-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ت-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فِتْنَة","root":"فتن","pos":"N","occurrence_count":34},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n32966","n32971"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%90%D8%AA%D9%92%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"trial"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"strife"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"civil war"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sedition"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tribulation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"charm"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"craze"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"crime"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"huisache, Vachellia farnesiana","tags":["singulative"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Related with seduction and revolt. Compare فَتَنَ (fatana, “to trial”)."},"ipa":["/fit.na/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32966","headword_ar":"فَتَنَهُ","root":"ftn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatonN","text_ar":"فَتْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) [and quasi-inf. n., in this and other senses,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitonapN","text_ar":"فِتْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He burned it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, * S, * M, K *) in the fire. (M.) Hence, [in the Kur li. 13,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawoma humo EalaY A@ln~aAri yufotanuwna","text_ar":"يَوْمَ هُمْ عَلَى ا@لنَّارِ يُفْتَنُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, * S, M, K *) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The day,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the day,"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to two different readings, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu","text_ar":"يَوْمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawoma","text_ar":"يَوْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the latter of which is the more common,)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when they shall be burned"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the fire"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of Hell]. (T.) And [in the Kur lxxxv. 10,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a A@l~a*iyna fatanuwA A@lomuw^ominiyna","text_ar":"اـِنَّ ا@لَّذِينَ فَتَنُوا ا@لْمُوْمِنِينَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@lomuw^ominaAti","text_ar":"وَا@لْمُوْمِنَاتِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily they who burned the believing men and the believing women"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S *) in the fire kindled in the trench, or pit; throwing them therein. (T.) This is said to be the primary signification of the verb. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He melted it with fire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put it into the fire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb,) namely, gold, (T, S, Msb,) and silver,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order to separate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distinguish,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the bad from the good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the good from the bad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to see what was its"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"degree of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b3-  And hence, accord. to Er-Rághib,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfatonu","text_ar":"الفَتْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The causing"},{"kind":"text","text":"a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to enter into fire"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by way of trial,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"probation"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in like manner"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into a state of punishment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affliction:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [and it is also used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the slaying"},{"kind":"text","text":"another; whence, in the Kur iv. 102,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino","text_ar":"اـِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xifotumo A^ano yafotinakumu A@l~a*iyna kafaruwA","text_ar":"خِفْتُمْ اَنْ يَفْتِنَكُمُ ا@لَّذِينَ كَفَرُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If ye fear that those who have disbelieved"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may slay you;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner in the Chapter of Yoonus [i. e. in x. 83],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ano yafotinahumo","text_ar":"اَنْ يَفْتِنَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"An yaqotulahumo","text_ar":"ان يَقْتُلَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T. [In the TA, these two exs. are misplaced, or something has been omitted before them by a copyist.]) ―         -b4-  [Hence also,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatanahu","text_ar":"فَتَنَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatonN","text_ar":"فَتْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, caused him to fall into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfitonap","text_ar":"الفِتْنَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trial;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affliction, distress,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hardship;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[generally meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an affliction whereby some good or evil quality is put to the test;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aifotatanahu","text_ar":"اِفْتَتَنَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ft~nhu","text_ar":"فتّنهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) but this, of which the inf. n. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tafotiynN","text_ar":"تَفْتِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", has an intensive signification; (S;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afotanahu","text_ar":"اَفْتَنَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) which last is rare, or rather, accord. to As, [though app. not in this sense, but in another, to be mentioned in what follows,] is not allowable: (TA:) the first of these verbs is trans. and intrans.: (S, K, TA:) you say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatana","text_ar":"فَتَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, T, S, K, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, T, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futuwnN","text_ar":"فُتُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, T, S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fell into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitonap","text_ar":"فِتْنَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"page_break","n":2335},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trial,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affliction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; (AZ, T, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aifotatana","text_ar":"اِفْتَتَنَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or the former signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he shifted from a good, to an evil, state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to En-Nadr, one says ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aifotatana","text_ar":"اِفْتَتَنَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aufotutina","text_ar":"اُفْتُتِنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", both meaning the same; and this is correct; but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatana","text_ar":"فَتَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as quasi-pass. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatanotuhu","text_ar":"فَتَنْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. as intrans.] is of weak authority: (T:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aufotutina","text_ar":"اُفْتُتِنَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of a man, [as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aifotatana","text_ar":"اِفْتَتَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futina","text_ar":"فُتِنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signify the same, (S, M,) accord. to AZ, (M,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was smitten by a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitonap","text_ar":"فِتْنَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trial,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that his wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"property,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his intellect, departed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and likewise"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was tried,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tested:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and accord. to AZ, one says, of a man, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ufotina","text_ar":"اُفْتِنَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [if not a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aufotutina","text_ar":"اُفْتُتِنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as above,] with damm, meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futina","text_ar":"فُتِنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatanahu","text_ar":"فَتَنَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futuwnN","text_ar":"فُتُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also as an inf. n.:] it is said in the Kur [xx. 41],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wafatan~aAka","text_ar":"وَفَتَنَّاكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futuwnFA","text_ar":"فُتُونًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And we tried thee with a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"severe"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trying:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the noun in this instance is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatonN","text_ar":"فَتْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitonapN","text_ar":"فِتْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", formed by disregard of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HujuwzN","text_ar":"حُجُوزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buduwrN","text_ar":"بُدُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"which are [said to be] pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HujozapN","text_ar":"حُجْزَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badorapN","text_ar":"بَدْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; so that the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meaning is, we tried thee with several sorts of trying:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and we purified thee with a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thorough"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an effectual"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purifying"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like that of gold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"silver, by means of fire"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) [in many instances]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatanahu","text_ar":"فَتَنَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", [inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatonN","text_ar":"فَتْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He tried,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tested, him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence, in the Kur ix. 127,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yufotanuwna","text_ar":"يُفْتَنُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are tried,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tested,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by being summoned to war, against unbelievers or the like; or, as some say, by the infliction of punishment or of some evil thing. (M.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatanotumo A^anofusakumo","text_ar":"فَتَنْتُمْ اَنْفُسَكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [lvii. 13], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ye caused yourselves to fall into trial and punishment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wahumo laA yufotanuwna","text_ar":"وَهُمْ لَا يُفْتَنُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur xxix. 1, is expl. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"While they are not tried in their persons and their possessions so that he who has true faith may be known from others by his patient endurance of trial."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) And the saying, in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~akumo tufotanuwna fiY Alqubuwri","text_ar":"اـِنَّكُمْ تُفْتَنُونَ فِى القُبُورِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily ye shall be tried,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tested, in the graves by"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the questioning of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two angels"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Munkar and Nekeer."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafotuwnN","text_ar":"مَفْتُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is said to be an inf. n., and syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitonapN","text_ar":"فِتْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiborapN","text_ar":"خِبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futuwnN","text_ar":"فُتُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(mentioned above as an inf. n. of the intrans. v."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatana","text_ar":"فَتَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"junuwnN","text_ar":"جُنُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as well as a pass. part. n.] ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatanahN","text_ar":"فَتَنَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatonN","text_ar":"فَتْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA, [or perhaps"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futuwnN","text_ar":"فُتُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the next following sentence]) also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to turn from,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the predicament in which he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the right course:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) whence, in the Kur [xvii. 75],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA_ino kaAduwA layafotinuwnaka Eani A@l~a*iY A^awoHayonaA","text_ar":"وَاـِنْ كَادُوا لَيَفْتِنُونَكَ عَنِ ا@لَّذِى اَوْحَيْنَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilayoka","text_ar":"اـِلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And verily they were near to"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their making thee to turn"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from that which we had revealed to thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: thus this saying has been explained. (TA.) [And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, seduced him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tempted him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus it may often be well rendered, agreeably with what next precedes and what next follows, and with explanations of its act. part. n. and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitonapN","text_ar":"فِتْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatana","text_ar":"فَتَنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaAlu Aln~aAsa","text_ar":"المَالُ النَّاسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futuwnN","text_ar":"فُتُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or perhaps"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatonN","text_ar":"فَتْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the next preceding sentence,] meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"property, inclined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attracted, to it, men,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mankind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futina fiY diynihi","text_ar":"فُتِنَ فِى دِينِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aufotutina","text_ar":"اُفْتُتِنَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", both in the pass. form,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He declined"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was made to decline"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the right way in"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his religion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatanahu","text_ar":"فَتَنَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor,"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatonN","text_ar":"فَتْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futuwnN","text_ar":"فُتُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it induced in him admiration,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasure;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, * K, * TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afotanahu","text_ar":"اَفْتَنَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[respecting which see what here follows]: (M, K:) and one says, of a woman,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatanatohu","text_ar":"فَتَنَتْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S,) meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She enamoured him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"captivated his heart;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she bereaved him of his heart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reason,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dal~ahatohu","text_ar":"دَلَّهَتْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [thus in several copies of the S, in one of my copies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~ahatohu","text_ar":"بَلَّهَتْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so affected him that"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he loved her;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afotanatohu","text_ar":"اَفْتَنَتْهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, S;) the former of the dial. of El-Hijáz, and the latter of the dial. of Nejd; (T, S; *) but ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aftnthu","text_ar":"افتنتهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aftnhu","text_ar":"افتنهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) was disallowed by As, (T, S, M,) and he paid no regard to a verse mentioned to him as an ex. thereof, (T,) [or] he ignored a verse cited to him as an ex. of the pass. part. n. from an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^urojuwzap","text_ar":"اُرْجُوزَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Ru-beh, not knowing it therein; (M;) most of the lexicologists, however, allow both: (T:) Sb says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatanahu","text_ar":"فَتَنَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he put"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"occasioned"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in him"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitonap","text_ar":"فِتْنَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aftnhu","text_ar":"افتنهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he caused"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfitonap","text_ar":"الفِتْنَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to come to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to affect him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (M;) or he said that the latter means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made him to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAtin","text_ar":"فَاتِن"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hazanahu","text_ar":"حَزَنَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and one says also, of a man,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futina bA@lomaroA^api","text_ar":"فُتِنَ با@لْمَرْاَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aufotutina","text_ar":"اُفْتُتِنَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[both meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was enamoured by the woman"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T.) ―         -b6-  And one says also, of a man,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatana","text_ar":"فَتَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futuwnN","text_ar":"فُتُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He desired"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfujuwr","text_ar":"الفُجُور"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the committing of adultery"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fornication"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (AZ, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatana A_ilaY","text_ar":"فَتَنَ اـِلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~isaA='i","text_ar":"النِّسَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futuwnN","text_ar":"فُتُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he desired"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfujuwr","text_ar":"الفُجُور"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with women"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the women;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futina A_ilayohin~a","text_ar":"فُتِنَ اـِلَيْهِنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","S","K","T","Msb","TA","AZ","Bd"]},{"entry_id":"n32971","headword_ar":"فِتْنَةٌ","root":"ftn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A burning with fire."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) ―         -b2-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"melting"},{"kind":"text","text":"of gold and of silver (K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order to separate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distinguish, the bad from the good."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And [hence, or] from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatana","text_ar":"فَتَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “ he melted, ” (T,) or from that verb as signifying “ he put into the fire, “ (Msb,) gold, and silver, “ for that purpose, ” (T, Msb,) it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A trial,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"probation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T, S, M, K, TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affliction, distress,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hardship;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and [particularly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an affliction whereby one is tried, proved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tested:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T, S, K, TA:) this is the sum of its meaning in the language of the Arabs: (T, TA: *) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trial whereby the condition of a man may be evinced:"},{"kind":"text","text":"this, accord. to Zj, may be the meaning in the Kur v. 45: (M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mean whereby the condition of a man is evinced, in respect of good"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of evil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull:) [hence it often means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a temptation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafotuwnN","text_ar":"مَفْتُونٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitonapN","text_ar":"فِتْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a trial:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitonapN","text_ar":"فِتْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitanN","text_ar":"فِتَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) It proceeds from God and from man: (Er-Rághib, TA:) [there are many instances of its proceeding from God in the Kur; for ex., in xxxvii. 61,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~aA","text_ar":"اـِنَّا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEalonaAhaA fitonapF lilZ~aAlimiyna","text_ar":"جَعَلْنَاهَا فِتْنَةً لِلظَّالِمِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily we have made it to be"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a trial"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the wrongdoers"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said in relation to the tree Ez-Zakkoom; the existence of which they disbelieved; for when they heard that it comes forth in the bottom of Hell, they said, Trees become burned in the fire; then how can they grow therein? (M.) [And hence] it signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Punishment, castigation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chastisement."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Slaughter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"civil war,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conflict occurring among people:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slaughter, and war, and faction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sedition, among the parties of the Muslims when they form themselves into parties:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discord, dissension,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difference of opinions, among the people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T, K.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A misleading;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"causing to err,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"go astray:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seduction;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"temptation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cause thereof; such as"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ornature, finery, show,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pomp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desires,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lusts, of the present life"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"world, whereby one is tried:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"children;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K, TA;) because one is tried thereby: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"women;"},{"kind":"text","text":"than whom, the Prophet said, there is no"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitonap","text_ar":"فِتْنَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"more harmful to men: (T:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cause of"},{"kind":"text","text":"one's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being pleased"},{"kind":"text","text":"with a thing; (T, M, K;) as in the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tajoEalonaA fitonapF liloqawomi A@lZ~aAlimiyna","text_ar":"لَا تَجْعَلْنَا فِتْنَةً لِلْقَوْمِ ا@لظَّالِمِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the Kur x. 85, i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Make not us to be a cause of pleasure"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2336},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the wrongdoing people"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning, make not them to prevail over us, so as to become pleased with their unbelief and to think that they are better than we. (T.) Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Madness, insanity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diabolical possession;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futuwnN","text_ar":"فُتُونٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafotuwnN","text_ar":"مَفْتُونٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Error;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deviation from the right way."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Infidelity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unbelief:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K:) thus in the saying, [in the Kur ii. 187,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@lofitonapu A^a$ad~u mina A@loqatoli","text_ar":"وَا@لْفِتْنَةُ اَشَدُّ مِنَ ا@لْقَتْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And infidelity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unbelief, is more excessive than slaughter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the like is said in ii. 214]. (T.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sin, a crime;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an act of disobedience for which one deserves punishment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Disgrace, shame,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ignominy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitonapu","text_ar":"فِتْنَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~adori","text_ar":"الصَّدْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwasowaAsu","text_ar":"الوَسْوَاسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The devil's prompting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suggesting, of some evil idea"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitonapu AlmaHoyaA","text_ar":"فِتْنَةُ المَحْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The being turned from the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"road:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitonapu AlmamaAti","text_ar":"فِتْنَةُ المَمَاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The being questioned in the grave"},{"kind":"text","text":"[by the two angels Munkar and Nekeer]:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitonapu AlD~ur~i","text_ar":"فِتْنَةُ الضُّرِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sword:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitotapu Als~ur~i","text_ar":"فِتْتَةُ السُّرِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Women."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfitonapu AlEamoyaA","text_ar":"الفِتْنَةُ العَمْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a phrase used in the present day as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Incurable evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trouble."},{"kind":"text","text":"]       -A2-  [It is also the name now commonly given to The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mimosa farnesiana"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Linn.; (Delile's Floræ Ægypt. Illustr. no. 962;) called by Forskål (Flora Ægypt. Arab. p. lxxvii.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mimosa scorpioïdes."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","T","Msb","IAar","S","M","Kull"]}]}}